b'' b'excerpts from rec.autos: 26-apr-93 re: review: ford tauru.. by mark' b' id bonds) writes:' b' b' gkoccasionally, i have trouble shifting into reverse. the shifter' b' gkrefuses to enter the gate, and i often grind the synchros trying to' b" gkget it into gear. i'll be watching this carefully in the next couple" b' gkof months.' b' b' enter 1st, wait seconds and then go into reverse. they use the same' b" synchros, and you'll never (at least i haven't) ground-em-to-fit when using" b' this technique.' b'' b' or do like the manual says and put it in 3rd first, then you can quickly' b' go into reverse... no waiting.' b'' b"one more way, which works in manual trans cars i've driven, and it is my" b'personal favorite (the other suggestions above are great, but try this' b'one, too).' b'' b'while pushing the shifter *gently* towards reverse, let the clutch out' b'slowly (right to the friction point) and the shifter will be pulled into' b"position. if you do it right, the car won't jump backward, nor will the" b'gears grind.... you will just glide back.' b'' b'-sam' 